The cabinet shall issue a certification as a radon laboratory to any person or entity that:
Submits a complete and accurate application for certification on a form prescribed by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation that includes the name of at least one (1) measurement contractor who is responsible for analytical activities;
Pays the certification fee as established by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation within the following restrictions:
An initial certification fee shall not exceed two hundred fifty dollars ($250);
An annual renewal fee shall not exceed two hundred fifty dollars ($250);
A duplicate certificate fee shall not exceed twenty dollars ($20); and
A late renewal fee shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
Submits a quality control program plan that meets the minimum standard operating procedures requirements established by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation;
Utilizes only cabinet-approved measurement devices and analytical services, and submits a description of each type of measurement device and analytical service utilized; and
Provides documentation of enrollment and good standing within a cabinet-approved independent laboratory accreditation program for each type of measurement device and analytical service utilized.
